paragraphs.text:
/* Finding distrubution of gender */
%spark.sql
select count(Cust_Gender),Cust_Gender
from sbank
--where Cust_Gender IS NOT NULL
group by Cust_Gender

/* Counting number of cutomers having same last date as primary customer */
%spark.sql
select count(Last_Date), Last_Date
from sbank
group by Last_Date
order by Last_Date asc

/* Distribution of customer identification as VIP, Individuals or students*/
%spark.sql
select count(Cust_Identification), Cust_Identification 
from sbank
group by Cust_Identification

/* Distribution of customer Type */
%spark.sql
select count(Cust_Type),Cust_Type
from sbank
group by Cust_Type

/* Average gross income for each type of customer identification */
%spark.sql
select avg(Gross_Income) as Avg_Gross_Income,  Cust_Identification 
from sbank
where Cust_Identification  is NOT NULL
group by Cust_Identification

/* Average gross income for each gener type */
%spark.sql
select avg(Gross_Income) as Avg_Gross_Income, Cust_Gender
from sbank
where Cust_Gender IS NOT NULL
group by Cust_Gender

/* Districution for gender and customer identification */
%spark.sql
select count(sexo) as Count_Gender, count(segmento) as Count_Cust_Identification, sexo as Gender, segmento as Cust_Identification
from sbank
where sexo IS NOT NULL
and segmento IS NOT NULL
group by sexo,segmento
